  "text": "Moderator which can also be referred to as independent factor in this study is to give direction of the relationship on the relation between recognition or appreciation and Job Satisfaction and Job Performance. According to Bennet's (2000) research on mediator and moderator variables provide useful information about how, why, or when a phenomenon occurs. For example, \"mediator\" is often used as if it meant \"predictor\". A mediator or moderator is a third variable that changes the association between an independent variable and an outcome variable [CITATION_1] . Thus, consideration of a mediator or moderator allows a more precise description of the relationship between independent and outcome variables. If a researcher fails to consider the possibility of a mediator or moderator effect in the data, a more exact explanation for an outcome may be missed.",
